旅鶇的食物40%為[[蚯蚓|蚯蚓]]、[[毛蟲|毛蟲]]和[[蚱蜢|蚱蜢]]等無脊椎動物，它們會在地表尋找這些動物為食<ref name="All About Birds"/>。另外的60%為植物果實，它們會集體覓食[[火棘屬|火棘屬]]植物的漿果，因為該屬植物成熟的果實含有酒精而喝醉，導致步履不穩甚至摔跤<ref name="ADW"/>。幼鳥則一般主要以柔軟的無脊椎動物為食。在沿海地區，''T. m. caurinus''還會在海灘上覓食小型軟體動物<ref name = Clement/>。

旅鶇可以利用聽覺、視覺、嗅覺甚至還可能包括觸覺來覓食，但以視覺為主<ref name= montgomerie>{{cite journal |last1=Montgomerie |first1=Robert |last2=Weatherhead |first2=Patrick J. |year=1997 |title=How robins ﬁnd worms |journal=Animal Behaviour |volume=54 |pages=143–151 |url=http://web2.uwindsor.ca/courses/biology/dmennill/360/article.pdf |format=PDF |doi=10.1006/anbe.1996.0411 |pmid=9268444 |issue=1 |access-date=2014-05-21 |archive-date=2020-10-25 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201025002030/http://web2.uwindsor.ca/courses/biology/dmennill/360/article.pdf |dead-url=no }}</ref>。常可以看到在草地上跑跑跳跳地并左右晃動腦袋來尋找食物的旅鶇。此外要尋找地下的食物就還是要依靠聽力<ref name= montgomerie2>{{cite journal |last1=Montgomerie |first1=Robert |last2=Weatherhead |first2=Patrick J. |year=1997 |title=How robins ﬁnd worms |journal=Animal Behaviour |volume=54 |page=149 |url=http://web2.uwindsor.ca/courses/biology/dmennill/360/article.pdf |format=PDF |doi=10.1006/anbe.1996.0411 |pmid=9268444 |access-date=2014-05-21 |archive-date=2020-10-25 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201025002030/http://web2.uwindsor.ca/courses/biology/dmennill/360/article.pdf |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

=== 威脅===
[[松鼠|松鼠]]、[[蛇|蛇]]和其他一些鳥類諸如[[冠藍鴉|冠藍鴉]]、[[暗冠藍鴉|暗冠藍鴉]]、[[擬椋鳥|擬椋鳥]]、[[美洲烏鴉|美洲烏鴉]]和[[渡鴉|渡鴉]]等會捕食幼年的旅鶇<ref name="ADW"/>。成年旅鶇的天敵主要是各種大小的[[鷹屬|鷹屬]]、[[隼|隼屬]]猛禽、貓和大型蛇類（尤其是[[食鼠蛇|食鼠蛇]]）<ref>{{cite journal|author=Cox, T. M. |year=1986|title=More on the bird-eating activities of the black rat snake, ''Elaphe obsoleta obsoleta'' (Say)|journal= North. Ohio Assoc. Herpetol. Notes |volume=14|pages=18–19}}</ref>，其中總共有28種猛禽會以旅鶇為食<ref>{{cite journal|author=Storer, R. W.|year=1966|title=Sexual dimorphism and food habits in three North American accipiters|journal=The Auk|volume=83|issue=3|pages=423–436|jstor=4083053|url=http://sora.unm.edu/node/21529|doi=10.2307/4083053|access-date=2014-05-21|archive-date=2021-01-07|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210107214411/https://sora.unm.edu/node/21529|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal |last1=Olendorff|first1=Richard R.|year=1976|title=The Food Habits of North American Golden Eagles|url=https://archive.org/details/sim_american-midland-naturalist_1976-01_95_1/page/231|journal=American Midland Naturalist|volume=95|issue=1|pages=231–236|jstor=2424254|doi=10.2307/2424254 }}</ref><ref>Bent, A. C. (1938). ''Life histories of North American birds of prey, pt. 2''. U.S. Natl. Mus. Bull. no. 170.</ref><ref>Mc Caffery, B. J., Booms, T. L., Doolittle, T. C., Broerman, F. R. E. D., Morgart, J. R., & Sowl, K. M. (2011). [http://peregrinefund.org/subsites/conference-gyr/proceedings/117-McCaffery.pdf "The ecology of Gyrfalcons ''Falco rusticolus'' on the Yukon-Kuskokwim Delta, Alaska"] {{Wayback|url=http://peregrinefund.org/subsites/conference-gyr/proceedings/117-McCaffery.pdf |date=20180602155327 }} in ''Gyrfalcons and Ptarmigan in a Changing World''. The Peregrine Fund, Boise, Idaho, USA. ISBN 978-1461129073.</ref><ref>{{cite journal|url=http://sora.unm.edu/sites/default/files/journals/wilson/v108n01/p0123-p0128.pdf|author=Holt, D. W., & Leroux, L. A.|year=1996|title=Diets of northern pygmy-owls and northern saw-whet owls in west-central Montana|journal=The Wilson Bulletin|pages=123–128|volume=108|issue=1|access-date=2014-05-21|archive-date=2021-02-13|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210213183310/https://sora.unm.edu/sites/default/files/journals/wilson/v108n01/p0123-p0128.pdf|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal|author=Campbell, R. W., & MacColl, M. D. |year=1978|title=Winter foods of snowy owls in Southwestern British Columbia|url=https://archive.org/details/sim_journal-of-wildlife-management_1978-01_42_1/page/190 |journal= The Journal of Wildlife Management|volume= 42|issue=1|pages= 190–192}}</ref>。繁殖季節的旅鶇因為容易分心而更容易被捕捉到。但在集群的時候就比較警惕，並會互相警戒<ref name="ADW"/>。

旅鶇不會接受[[牛鸝屬|牛鸝屬]]鳥類的[[巢寄生|寄生]]卵，即使這些卵被成功孵化，幼鳥通常也不可能活到羽翼豐滿<ref name= Wolfe>{{cite journal |last= Wolfe |first= Donald H., |date= December 1994 |title= Brown-headed Cowbirds fledged from Barn Swallow and American Robin nests |journal= The Wilson Bulletin |jstor= 4163497 |volume= 106 |issue= 4 |pages= 764–766 |url= http://sora.unm.edu/node/131255 |access-date= 2014-05-21 |archive-date= 2021-01-07 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20210107214425/https://sora.unm.edu/node/131255 |dead-url= no }}</ref>。旅鶇是[[西尼羅河病毒|西尼羅河病毒]]的寄主，而這種病毒會殺死[[烏鴉|烏鴉]]和[[松雞|松雞]]，它們也很可能通過蚊子將這種病毒傳染給了人類<ref name =NationalScienceFoundation2009>National Science Foundation: West Nile Virus: The Search for Answers in Chicago’s Suburbs</ref><ref name =ScienceNews>[http://www.sciencedaily.com/releases/2009/02/090220191318.htm Diversity Of Birds Buffer Against West Nile Virus] {{Wayback|url=http://www.sciencedaily.com/releases/2009/02/090220191318.htm |date=20210211184434 }}. Sciencedaily.com (2009-03-06). Retrieved on 2012-08-23.</ref>。此外，在一項關於105隻旅鶇幼鳥寄生蟲的試驗中，77.1%的幼鳥被發現至少感染了一種或兩種寄生蟲，其中[[比翼屬|比翼屬]]的寄生蟲尤為常見，共57.1%的幼鳥感染了比翼屬寄生蟲<ref name= Welt>{{cite journal |last1=Welte |first1=S. C. |last2=Kirkpatrick |first2=C. E. |year=1986 |title=Syngamiasis in juvenile American Robins (''Turdus migratorius''), with a note on the prevalence of other fecal parasites |journal=Avian Disease |volume=30 |issue=4 |pages=736–9 |doi=10.2307/1590578 |jstor=1590578 |pmid=2949729}}</ref>。

=== 繁殖===
[[File:Robin_eggs_flying_in_3_weeks_-_by_Volkan_Yuksel.jpg|left]]
[[File:Robin_chick_2_Galawebdesign.jpg|thumb]]
在夏季過冬返回之後，旅鶇就會馬上開始繁殖，是北美最早開始繁殖的鳥類之一。四月至七月間產二至五枚卵<ref name="ADW"/><ref name = IWRC/>。它們的巢一般建造在地面以上{{Convert|1.5|to|4.5|m|ft}}的灌木叢中，有時也會集群在幾枝樹杈上築巢。只有雌性旅鶇才會築巢，材料主要是雜草、樹枝和羽毛，外部塗抹泥巴，裡面加上細草等柔軟襯墊。在靠北的地區，最早的巢筑在[[常绿植物|常青樹]]上，而後來的巢就只能筑在[[落葉樹|落葉樹]]上了。一些人類的屋簷下也可以找到旅鶇的巢<ref>{{cite web| title = AMERICAN ROBIN| publisher = The Texas Breeding Bird Atlas| url = http://txtbba.tamu.edu/species-accounts/american-robin/| accessdate = 2014-05-23| archive-date = 2021-01-23| archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20210123002827/https://txtbba.tamu.edu/species-accounts/american-robin/| dead-url = no}}</ref>。

它們的卵多為橢圓形，顏色為淺藍。兩周後幼鳥就可以破殼而出，再過兩星期就可以飛翔了。剛出生的雛兒身體赤裸，需要數天時間才可以睜開眼睛<ref name = IWRC>{{cite web |title=American Robin (''Turdus migratorius'') |url=http://www.iwrc-online.org/kids/Facts/Birds/robin.htm |publisher=International Wildlife Rehabilitation Council |accessdate=2008-01-21 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20071031214806/http://www.iwrc-online.org/kids/Facts/Birds/robin.htm |archive-date=2007-10-31 |dead-url=yes }}</ref>。成鳥會帶走巢中的包括幼鳥白色糞便在內的廢棄物質<ref name="ADW"/>。即使可以飛翔，幼鳥仍然會跟隨成鳥一段時間，並從後者那裡乞取食物<ref name="ADW"/>。

通過[[鳥足帶|鳥足帶]]，研究者發現只有二成幼鳥可以活過第一年<ref name="ADW"/>。而其平均壽命只有兩年，壽命最長的旅鶇則活了14年<ref name="ADW"/>。

=== 鳴叫===
{{listen|filename=Turdus-migratorius-003.ogg|title=旅鶇|description=旅鶇在清晨的鳴叫聲，背景裡還有微弱的山雀的歌聲}}
像同屬的其他鳥類一樣，雄性旅鶇可以叫很长时间，叫声中会有短暂的停顿。它们的叫声听起来比较欢快，聲調多变<ref name="Bull87">{{cite book |author=Bull J, Farrand, J Jr |title=Audubon Society Field Guide to North American Birds:Eastern Region |url=https://archive.org/details/audubonsocietyfi0000bull |year=1987 |publisher=Alfred A. Knopf |page = [https://archive.org/details/audubonsocietyfi0000bull/page/469 469]|location=New York |isbn=0-394-41405-5 }}</ref>。在不同的時間、地區其叫聲也會有差別。它们一般在每年三月至七月末八月初鸣叫，東部地區的一些旅鶇在九月還會持續鳴叫。它們也是太陽初升時最早開始鳴叫的鳥類，直到夜晚聲音不絕，而地點一般是高高的樹枝上<ref name="ADW"/>。在旅鶇的各個亞種中，''T. m. confinis''的叫聲較其他亞種為弱，也不甚清晰<ref name=Clement/>。

除去持續的叫聲外，旅鶇也會發出特定的聲音用以交流、示警等。<ref name=Clement/>

== 在人類文化中 ==

旅鶇不僅是美國康涅狄格州、密歇根州和威斯康星州的州鳥<ref name="50 States2">{{cite web|url=http://www.50states.com/dc.htm|author=50 States|title=50 States|accessdate=2007-07-25|archive-date=2012-07-10|archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/693m8zLZB?url=http://www.50states.com/dc.htm|dead-url=no}}</ref>，1986年也曾被印在“加拿大鳥類系列”的2[[加拿大元|加拿大元]]紙鈔上，但這種紙鈔已被國家收回<ref name="cpm">{{cite web|url=http://www.cdnpapermoney.com/English/BoC/1986_2.htm|title=Canadian Paper Money|author=Canadian Paper Money Society|accessdate=2008-01-18|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080103221320/http://www.cdnpapermoney.com/English/BoC/1986_2.htm|archivedate=2008年1月3日|deadurl=yes}}</ref>。知更鳥蛋藍就是因為與旅鶇的卵顏色相同而得名<ref name=OED>{{Cite encyclopedia| title=Robin|encyclopedia=Oxford English Dictionary|editor=Simpson, J. and  Weiner, E.| year=1989 |edition= 2nd| location=Oxford |publisher=Clarendon Press|isbn= 0-19-861186-2}}</ref>。

在[[美國土著|美國土著]]居民的神話中，旅鶇也有著一定的地位。與歐洲的知更鳥類似，美國土著传说旅鶇是因為想要吹散威脅著一位男性土著和一名男孩生命的火焰，所以胸部才会变得如此之紅<ref>{{cite book | last = Fox| first = Florence C. | year = 1906 | title = The Indian Primer (Fox's Indian Primer) | publisher = American Book Company | pages = 88–95 | url =http://books.google.com/?id=gb4AAAAAYAAJ| accessdate =2011-05-22 }}</ref>。[[特林基特人|特林基特人]]將旅鶇當做[[文化英雄|文化英雄]]，並以其名來讚揚有他們那樣的歌聲的人<ref name = "Cooper92">{{cite book |last=Cooper |first=JC |title=Symbolic and Mythological Animals |page=194 |year=1992 |publisher= Aquarian Press |location=London |isbn=1-85538-118-4}}</ref>。

1930年代中期，一個旅鶇家族因為築巢於[[水牛城|水牛城]]和[[伊利堡|伊利堡]]之間的[[和平橋_(尼亞加拉河)|和平橋]]上而被稱為“和平橋知更鳥”（Peace Bridge robins）。<ref>The Canadian Press. [http://select.nytimes.com/gst/abstract.html?res=FB0B13FF3D5E167B93C0A8178FD85F428385F9&scp=1&sq=Famous+robins+return&st=p "Famous robins return to nest at Peace Bridge"] {{Wayback|url=http://select.nytimes.com/gst/abstract.html?res=FB0B13FF3D5E167B93C0A8178FD85F428385F9&scp=1&sq=Famous+robins+return&st=p |date=20140521153649 }}, ''The New York Times''. 12 April 1936. Page 6.</ref>

旅鶇也被北美洲的人們當做春天的象征<ref>{{cite book |last1=Durant |first1=Alan |last2=Fabb |first2=Nigel |year=1990 |title=Literary Studies in Action |publisher=Routledge |url=http://books.google.com/?id=ZqAOAAAAQAAJ&pg=PA75 |accessdate=2008-02-01 |isbn=978-0-415-02945-2 |page=75}}</ref>。[[埃米莉·狄更生|埃米莉·狄更生]]曾專門寫過一首詩，名為“我如此害怕第一隻知更鳥”（I Dreaded That First Robin So）。此外[[威廉·亨利·德拉蒙德|威廉·亨利·德拉蒙德]]也曾寫過一首叫做“第一隻知更鳥”（The First Robin）的詩，根據德拉蒙德的妻子所述，這首詩來的灵感源自魁北克迷信，當地人認為第一個看到第一隻知更鳥的人會帶來好運<ref>{{cite book |last1=Drummond |first1=William Henry |others=Preface by May Harvey Drummond |year=1908 |title=The Great Fight |publisher=G. P. Putnam's Sons |pages=xi, 81–86 |url=http://books.google.com/?id=qZYOAAAAIAAJ |accessdate=2008-02-01}}</ref>。[[哈利·M·伍茲|哈利·M·伍茲]]曾寫過一首名為“When the Red, Red Robin (Comes Bob, Bob, Bobbin' Along)”的歌曲，這首歌在1926年大為流行。<ref>{{cite web | title = Cover of sheet music for "When the Red, Red Robin Comes Bob, Bob, Bobbing Along" – Ruth Etting | work = The Ruth Etting Web Site | origyear = 1997 | date = 2007 | url = http://ruthetting.com/when-the-red-red-robin/ | accessdate = 2012-04-15 | archive-date = 2020-12-19 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20201219094003/http://ruthetting.com/when-the-red-red-robin/ | dead-url = no }}</ref>

美國漫畫中的超級英雄[[羅賓_(漫畫)|羅賓]]之所以叫“羅賓”（Robin），就是因為他出生在第一隻美洲知更鳥到來的那一天。<ref>{{cite journal | last=Groth | first=Gary | date=2005-10-15 | title=Jerry Robinson | journal=The Comics Journal | issue=271 | url=http://www.tcj.com/index.php?option=com_content&task=view&id=350&Itemid=48 | accessdate=2008-02-07 | archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080111224537/http://www.tcj.com/index.php?option=com_content&task=view&id=350&Itemid=48 | archivedate=2008年1月11日 | deadurl=no | quote=I had a vision of Robin Hood just as Wyeth drew him in his costume, and that's what I quickly sketched out when I suggested [the name] Robin, which they seemed to like, and then showed them the costume. }}</ref><ref>{{cite web | last=Ringgenberg | first=Steven | title=Jerry Robinson: January 1st, 1922 – December 7th, 2011 | url=http://www.tcj.com/jerry-robinson-january-1st-1922-december-7th-2011/ | work=tcj.com | accessdate=2013-04-18 | date=2011-12-13 | quote=Robinson added much to the luster of the Batman legend, including coming up with the name Robin the Boy Wonder (inspired by Robin Hood), and designing his costume (inspired by the N.C. Wyeth painting Robin Meets Maid Marian). | archive-date=2021-02-12 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210212001557/http://www.tcj.com/jerry-robinson-january-1st-1922-december-7th-2011/ | dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{Cite comic | writer=Bridwell, E. Nelson | penciller=Andru, Ross | inker=Esposito, Mike | story=The Origin of Robin | title=Batman | volume= 1 | issue = 213 | date=July–August 1969 | publisher=[[DC_Comics|DC Comics]]}}</ref>

